org.flexiblepower.ral.drivers.dishwasher

Interface DishwasherState

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ResourceState

    public interface DishwasherState
extends ResourceState
    The DishwasherState that describes the current state of a dishwasher. In general there are 3 options:
    latestStartTime startTime program Meaning
    null null null The dishwasher is off or no program has been selected. In this case there is nothing to control.
    not null null not null The dishwasher is on with a selected program that has been delayed. It can be started anywhere between now and the latestStartTime.
    ?? not null not null The program has started at the startTime and it can not be interrupted anymore.

        java.util.Date getLatestStartTime()

      • getStartTime

        java.util.Date getStartTime()
        Returns:
        The time at which the program has been started, or null if it hasn't been started yet.

      • getProgram

        java.lang.String getProgram()
        Returns:
        The unique name of the selected program. This will be used for display purposes and in the DishwasherControlParameters.getProgram() to make sure that this program will be started. This can be null when the dishwasher is off or no program has been selected.
